<p>That category of things that we call racist does not exclude things simply because they are realistic. Political correctness isn't about being <em>fair</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35vy"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35vy" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35vy')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35vy" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35vy')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35vy" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35vy?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35vy" href="#35qa" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35vy" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35vy')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35vy class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35vy" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_35vy" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_35vy" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35yy" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35yy" class="parent"><a name="35yy" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35yy" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35yy" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35yy" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Misha/">Misha</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">16 December 2010 06:34:45PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35yy'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35yy')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35yy" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35yy" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Misha/">Misha</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">16 December 2010 06:34:45PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35yy'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35yy'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35yy')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35yy" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I would actually call a statement racist if it's primarily justified by racism (in which case it will be realistic only if it happens to be so accidentally). Since "racist" has a lot of negative connotations, it isn't useful to call something racist if you plan to agree with it, and therefore if I had to make a racially-based realistic statement, I'd call it something dumb like a racially-based realistic statement.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35yy"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35yy" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35yy')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35yy" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35yy')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35yy" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35yy?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35yy" href="#35vy" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35yy" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35yy')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35yy class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35yy" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35qk" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35qk" class="parent"><a name="35qk" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35qk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35qk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35qk" href="http://lesswrong.com