('t1_321l')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_321l" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That reminds me: when I was little, there was a puzzle in a happy meal that said, "Rearrange these letters to spell something that can make a canoe sink: ELAK."  The correct answer, of course, was "leak".  I was upset, because my answer was "a elk".  (And now that I think about it, if you draw this as a causal diagram, "lake" should be a valid answer too.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_321l"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_321l" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_321l')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_321l" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_321l')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_321l" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/321l?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_321l" href="#321g" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_321l" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_321l')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_321l class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_321l" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_321l" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_321l" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_3232" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_3232" class="parent"><a name="3232" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_3232" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_3232" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_3232" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Benquo/">Benquo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 08:12:07PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_3232'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_3232')">[+] (0 children)</a