<p>And in middle aged people and old people too. :)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_3299"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_3299" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_3299')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_3299" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_3299')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_3299" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/3299?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_3299" href="#3292" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_3299" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_3299')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_3299 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_3299" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32b3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32b3" class="parent"><a name="32b3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32b3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32b3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32b3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 04:45:27PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32b3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32b3')">[+] (14 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32b3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32b3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/shokwave/">shokwave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 04:45:27PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32b3'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32b3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32b3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32b3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The premise is true and generally accepted as such; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Structure_of_Scientific_Revolutions" rel="nofollow">a slightly more formal treatment</a> was given by Kuhn, but it amounts roughly to "new scientists produce advancements, old scientists stick to dogma, the status of oldies is so powerful they have to die or retire for advancements to prosper."</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32b3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32b3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32b3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32b3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32b3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32b3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32b3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32b3" href="#3292" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32b3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32b3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32b3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32b3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32b3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32b3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35t2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35t2" class="parent"><a name="35t2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35t2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35t2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35t2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:47:07PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t2'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35t2')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35t2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35t2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:47:07PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35t2'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t2'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35t2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35t2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Shortly after "Structure of Scientific Revolutions", there was a paradigm shift in geology: plate tectonics.  Which went from fringe to scientific consensus in, as I understand it, well under a decade thanks to overwhelming evidence.  Did unusually many geologists die that decade?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35t2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35t2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35t2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35t2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35t2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35t2" href="#32b3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35t2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35t2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35t2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35t2" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32gd" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32gd" class="parent"><a name="32gd" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32gd" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32gd" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32gd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 03:28:52AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32gd'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32gd')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32gd" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32gd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 03:28:52AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32gd'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32gd'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32gd')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32gd" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Kuhn did not say that. His notion of paradigm advancement had a lot to do with a lot of other things. His canonical example of paradigm change (the Copernican revolution) had people actively changing their minds even in his narrative. And there are a lot of problems with his story of how things went, see for example <a href="http://thonyc.wordpress.com/2010/11/12/galileo%E2%80%99s-great-bluff-and-part-of-the-reason-why-kuhn-is-wrong/" rel="nofollow">this essay</a>.</p>

<p>Furthermore, in many other shifts where new theories came into play, the overall trend happened with many old people accepting the new theory. Thus for example, Einstein's special relativity was accepted by many older physicists.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32gd"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32gd" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32gd')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32gd" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32gd')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32gd" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32gd?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32gd" href="#32b3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32gd" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32gd')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32gd class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32gd" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32gd" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32gd" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32sv" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_32sv" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_32sv" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32sv" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_32sv" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_32sv" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_32sv" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_37k', ['32sv'], 7)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(4 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32sv"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32sv" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32ba" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32ba" class="parent"><a name="32ba" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32ba" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32ba" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32ba" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 05:02:02PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ba'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32ba')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32ba" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32ba" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 05:02:02PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32ba'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ba'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32ba')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32ba" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I hope there have been some changes in the way scientists work since the 1960s. Also I hope that it depends on the specific field.</p>

<p>As a conclusion of the initial argument one could add time limits to tenure, but please lets not argue for killing off scientists justs for being to old.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32ba"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32ba" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ba')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32ba" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ba')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32ba" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32ba?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32ba" href="#32b3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32ba" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32ba')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32ba class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32ba" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32ba" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32ba" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32em" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32em" class="parent"><a name="32em" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32em" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32em" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32em" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/soreff/">soreff</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 11:21:03PM</span><span class="votes " >12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32em'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32em')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32em" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32em" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/soreff/">soreff</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 11:21:03PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32em'>12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32em'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32em')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32em" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>time limits to tenure</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Nice way to put it!  To phrase it another way:</p>

<p>To argue in favor of mortality because of fears of entrenched conservatives
is to demand capital punishment where term limits would suffice.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32em"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32em" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32em')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32em" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32em')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32em" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32em?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32em" href="#32ba" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32em" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32em')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32em class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32em" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32em" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32em" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32fz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32fz" class="parent"><a name="32fz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32fz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32fz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32fz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 02:30:53AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32fz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32fz')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32fz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32fz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 02:30:53AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32fz'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32fz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32fz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32fz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Thank you!</p>

<p>Try to get someone to put it in these words. Usually no one demands the killing of professors, or even mentions how he likes to have old people die from neglect.</p>

<p>If someone boldly states that he wants all these old people to die to free up space, or what ever, than you probably found a person you do not actually want to have a discussion with.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32fz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32fz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32fz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32fz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32fz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32fz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32fz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32fz" href="#32em" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32fz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32fz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32fz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32fz" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32g1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32g1" class="parent"><a name="32g1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32g1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32g1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32g1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 02:35:36AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32g1'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32g1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32g1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32g1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/MartinB/">MartinB</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 02:35:36AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32g1'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32g1'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32g1')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32g1" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I hope there have been some changes in the way scientists work since the 1960s.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I completely forgot about a very important point. When rejuvenation actually works, then it might also make the brain work better, younger and so on.
If it is true, that great scientists do their most important work before reaching age X, then after a rejuvenation they might be able to do even more with their good as new brain + more experience.
Then it would not be a matter of getting rid of holders of old ideas, but find a way to deal with people that have an unreachable time advantage, that cannot be made up. It would be good for society to keep experienced mind in work.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32g1"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32g1" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32g1')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32g1" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32g1')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32g1" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32g1?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32g1" href="#32ba" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32g1" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32g1')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32g1 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32g1" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32c9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32c9" class="parent"><a name="32c9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32c9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32c9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32c9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 06:53:03PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32c9'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32c9')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32c9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32c9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Perplexed/">Perplexed</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 06:53:03PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32c9'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32c9'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32c9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32c9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>No real need to kill them off, as long as new ones are being born.  Unanimity is nice, but simple majorities can usually get the job done.</p>

<p>As for your time limits idea, I might go further, and send everybody back to school to get a new PhD every 100 years: in a new field, at a different school, <em>in a different language</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32c9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32c9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32c9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32c9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32c9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32c9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32c9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32c9" href="#32ba" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32c9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32c9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32c9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32c9" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32c9" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32c9" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32l3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32l3" class="parent"><a name="32l3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32l3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32l3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32l3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/paper-machine/">paper-machine</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 December 2010 05:18:26PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32l3'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32l3')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32l3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32l3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/paper-machine/">paper-machine</a></span></strong></span><span class="co