<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ma_Jun" rel="nofollow">Ma Jun</a>, inventor or reinventor of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Pointing_Chariot" rel="nofollow">South Pointing Chariot</a> and the differential gear.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31wg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31wg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31wg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31wg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31wg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31wg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31wg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31wg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31wg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31wg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31wg" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31wg" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31wg" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31zn" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31zn" class="parent"><a name="31zn" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31zn" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31zn" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31zn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlanCrowe/">AlanCrowe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 03:17:01PM</span><span class="votes " >10 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31zn'] = ['9 points', '10 points', '11 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31zn')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31zn" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_31zn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlanCrowe/">AlanCrowe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 03:17:01PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_31zn'>10 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31zn'] = ['9 points', '10 points', '11 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_31zn')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31zn" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The word <em>empty</em> spoils the quotation. The point is that</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Powerful arguments with words cannot compete with a test which will show practical results</p>
</blockquote>

<p>or</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Good arguments with words that lose to a test which shows practical results are reduced thereby to empty arguments.</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31zn"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31zn" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31zn')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31zn" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31zn')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31zn" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31zn?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_31zn" href="#31wg" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31zn" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31zn')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31zn class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31zn" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31zn" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31zn" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_320m" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_320m" class="parent"><a name="320m" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_320m" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_320m" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_320m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Tesseract/">Tesseract</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:41:18PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320m'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_320m')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_320m" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_320m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Tesseract/">Tesseract</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:41:18PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_320m'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320m'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_320m')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_320m" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I read it as</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Arguments with words are inherently empty, and therefore cannot compare with a test which will show practical results.</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_320m"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_320m" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320m')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_320m" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320m')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_320m" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/320m?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_320m" href="#31zn" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_320m" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_320m')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_320m class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_320m" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31x0" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31x0" class="parent"><a name="31x0" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31x0" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31x0" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31x0" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 08:05:15AM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31x0'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31x0')">[+] (18 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31x0" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_31x0" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 08:05:15AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_31x0'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31x0'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_31x0')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31x0" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>| Theory and practice sometimes clash. And when that happens, theory loses. Every single time.</p>

<p>-- Linus Torvalds</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31x0"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31x0" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31x0')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31x0" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31x0')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31x0" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31x0?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31x0" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31x0')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31x0 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31x0" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31x0" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31x0" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35sz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35sz" class="parent"><a name="35sz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35sz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35sz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35sz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:43:13PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35sz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35sz')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35sz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35sz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:43:13PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35sz'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35sz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35sz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35sz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>In my experience, most people who say something like this mean "To hell with your longer-term thinking, look at the short-term success my short-term thinking has got me!"</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35sz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35sz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35sz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35sz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35sz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35sz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35sz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35sz" href="#31x0" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35sz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35sz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35sz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35sz" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_35sz" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_35sz" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35t5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35t5" class="parent"><a name="35t5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35t5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35t5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35t5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:54:06PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t5'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35t5')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35t5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35t5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:54:06PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35t5'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t5'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35t5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35t5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That's a good point. However, Torvalds specifically has got some solid long-term success as well to his credit.</p>

<p>And in programming in particular, I think there's a lot to be said for avoiding elegance creep.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35t5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35t5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35t5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35t5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35t5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35t5" href="#35sz" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35t5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35t5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35t5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35t5" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_35t5" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_35t5" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35t6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35t6" class="parent"><a name="35t6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35t6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35t6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35t6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:57:52PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t6'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35t6')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35t6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35t6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ciphergoth/">ciphergoth</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 10:57:52PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35t6'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35t6'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35t6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35t6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Sure, but I think the same category contains his disdain for the "license purists" who criticized his choice of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BitKeeper" rel="nofollow">BitKeeper</a>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35t6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35t6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35t6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35t6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35t6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35t6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35t6" href="#35t5" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35t6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35t6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35t6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35t6" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_35t6" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_35t6" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_35tc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_35tc" class="parent"><a name="35tc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_35tc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_35tc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_35tc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 11:20:49PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35tc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_35tc')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_35tc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_35tc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">15 December 2010 11:20:49PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_35tc'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_35tc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_35tc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_35tc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Thanks for the reference, I hadn't heard about that controversy before. Reading <a href="http://www.theregister.co.uk/2005/04/14/torvalds_attacks_tridgell/" rel="nofollow">this article</a> linked from that WP page reduces my respect for Torvalds a fair bit.</p>

<p>Luckily for everybody, though, the end result of the kerfluffle was the excellent git software.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_35tc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_35tc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35tc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_35tc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_35tc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_35tc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/35tc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_35tc" href="#35t6" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_35tc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_35tc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_35tc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_35tc" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31y4" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31y4" class="parent"><a name="31y4" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31y4" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31y4" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31y4" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:48:22AM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31y4'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31y4')">[+] (11 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31y4" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_31y4" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:48:22AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_31y4'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31y4'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_31y4')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31y4" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I felt a desire to argue against this quote, but of course a better idea would be to ask what it means.</p>

<p>I'm guessing that "practice" means "the way people are solving this problem now," while "theory" means "the study of what makes a problem-solving method good."</p>

<p>If theorists invent some method that they think is good, but which has already been rejected by practitioners, then I would guess that the theorists have a wrong notion of "good," and they should update their theory on the evidence. If the theorists invent a <em>new</em> method, then there is a chance that it is an improvement, and it may catch on.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31y4"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31y4" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31y4')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31y4" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31y4')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31y4" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31y4?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_31y4" href="#31x0" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31y4" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31y4')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31y4 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31y4" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31y4" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31y4" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_326t" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_326t" class="parent"><a name="326t" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_326t" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_326t" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_326t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Gabriel/">Gabriel</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 03:43:46AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_326t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_326t')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_326t" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_326t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Gabriel/">Gabriel</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 03:43:46AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_326t'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_326t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_326t')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_326t" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>If theorists invent some method that they think is good, but which has already been rejected by practitioners, then I would guess that the theorists have a wrong notion of "good," and they should update their theory on the evidence.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Practitioners can reject an idea for wrong reasons -- for example, because it seems weird and runs contrary to how things were always done.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_326t"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_326t" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_326t')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_326t" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_326t')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_326t" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/326t?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_326t" href="#31y4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_326t" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_326t')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_326t class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_326t" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_320c" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_320c" class="parent"><a name="320c" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_320c" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_320c" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_320c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gerg/">gerg</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:21:35PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320c'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_320c')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_320c" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_320c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gerg/">gerg</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:21:35PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_320c'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320c'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_320c')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_320c" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>My first reading of this quote was essentially <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/hs/think_like_reality/">&quot;the map loses to the terrain&quot;</a>. I interpreted "theory" as "our beliefs" and "practice" as "reality".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_320c"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_320c" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320c')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_320c" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320c')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_320c" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/320c?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_320c" href="#31y4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_320c" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_320c')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_320c class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_320c" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_320c" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_320c" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_324c" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_324c" class="parent"><a name="324c" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_324c" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_324c" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_324c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 09:45:03PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324c'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_324c')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_324c" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_324c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 09:45:03PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_324c'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324c'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_324c')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_324c" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If your beliefs are defeated whenever they clash with reality, then you have attained a mastery of rationality that very few humans achieve. Torvalds' quote looks to me like an "is" statement rather than an "ought" statement, so I can't agree with your interpretation.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_324c"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_324c" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324c')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_324c" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324c')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_324c" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/324c?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_324c" href="#320c" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_324c" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_324c')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_324c class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_324c" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_324c" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_324c" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_325a" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_325a" class="parent"><a name="325a" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_325a" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_325a" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_325a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/David_Gerard/">David_Gerard</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:48:19PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_325a'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_325a')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_325a" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_325a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/David_Gerard/">David_Gerard</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:48:19PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_325a'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_325a'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_325a')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_325a" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>He's talking about the status of the code in question in his Linux tree, the one everyone in the world pulls from, so in that context he does in fact have the power to make his opinions reality ...</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_325a"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_325a" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_325a')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_325a" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_325a')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_325a" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/325a?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_325a" href="#324c" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_325a" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_325a')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_325a class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_325a" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_325a" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_325a" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_328n" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_328n" class="parent"><a name="328n" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_328n" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_328n" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_328n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 09:49:39AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_328n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_328n')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_328n" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_328n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 09:49:39AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_328n'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_328n'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_328n')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_328n" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>According to gerg's interpretation, you're saying that Torvalds' theory wins against practice, which contradicts Torvalds' statement.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_328n"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_328n" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_328n')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_328n" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_328n')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_328n" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/328n?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_328n" href="#325a" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_328n" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_328n')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_328n class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_328n" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_328n" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_328n" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32rz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32rz" class="parent"><a name="32rz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32rz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32rz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32rz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 December 2010 02:18:37PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32rz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32rz')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32rz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32rz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 December 2010 02:18:37PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32rz'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32rz'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32rz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32rz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I don't think that quite jives. The situation seems to be the opposite: Torvalds' practice (the Linux code base, and its quite healthy community of contributors and users, who would be annoyed if ext4 programs stopped working suddenly) is winning against theory (the notion that the API policy of the Linux kernel should be revised more in favor of elegance over compatibility).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32rz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32rz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32rz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32rz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32rz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32rz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32rz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32rz" href="#328n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32rz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32rz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32rz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32rz" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32rz" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32rz" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32ux" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32ux" class="parent"><a name="32ux" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32ux" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32ux" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32ux" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 December 2010 09:05:57PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ux'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32ux')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32ux" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32ux" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">06 December 2010 09:05:57PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32ux'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ux'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32ux')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32ux" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I've been assuming that this subthread is about gerg's interpretation. Are you claiming that interpretation is correct, and offering some clarification, or are you just offering a different interpretation?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32ux"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32ux" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ux')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32ux" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ux')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32ux" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32ux?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32ux" href="#32rz" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32ux" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32ux')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32ux class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32ux" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32ux" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32ux" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_332y" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_332y" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_332y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_332y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_332y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_332y" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_332y" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_37k', ['332y'], 8)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_332y"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_332y" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_33k7" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_33k7" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_33k7" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_33k7" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_33k7" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_33k7" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_33k7" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_37k', ['33k7'], 4)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_33k7"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_33k7" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31yc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31yc" class="parent"><a name="31yc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31yc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31yc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31yc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/David_Gerard/">David_Gerard</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 12:00:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31yc'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31yc')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31yc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_31yc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/David_Gerard/">David_Gerard</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 12:00:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_31yc'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31yc'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_31yc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31yc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Torvalds is an engineer applying engineer's thinking, and here "practice" means engineering. The <a href="http://lkml.org/lkml/2009/3/25/632" rel="nofollow">context</a> was problems with a particularly awful API that just wasn't fit for purpose, but which had twenty years' encrusted usage to work around. He was responding to an ext4 filesystem programmer who was complaining that KDE4 users suffering dataloss on ext4 just weren't using the bad API the way he thought they should, even though other filesystems did not exhibit the dataloss.</p>

<p>I must confess that, reading the email, I don't see how he derives the last line from what he's saying above ... it doesn't seem to follow from taking about a 20-years-encrusted SNAFU. Perhaps it does follow from a programmer demanding people use an API the way he thinks they should, rather than the way everyone conventionally had for two decades. Real-world use winning over abstractions of how things should be:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>So rather than come up with new barriers that nobody will use, filesystem people should aim to make "badly written" code "just work" unless people are really really unlucky. Because like it or not, that's what 99% of all code is.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>It is, however, a widely-quoted statement - it resonates with people somehow. This is not, of course, the same as constituting or being about rationality.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31yc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31yc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31yc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31yc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31yc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31yc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31yc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_31yc" href="#31y4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31yc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31yc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31yc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31yc" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31yc" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31yc" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32ct" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32ct" class="parent"><a name="32ct" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32ct" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32ct" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32ct" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:10:04PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ct'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32ct')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32ct" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32ct" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:10:04PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32ct'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32ct'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32ct')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32ct" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's about rationality on the grounds that the filesystem programmer had lost sight of the necessity of <em>winning</em>; in this case, putting out code that actually works, rather than code that makes the programmer feel good.</p>

<p>It's painful to write clunky APIs, and pleasant to write elegant APIs... but that doesn't mean much if your elegant code would just be thrown away on release because everyone's already using the existing API.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32ct"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32ct" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ct')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32ct" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32ct')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32ct" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32ct?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32ct" href="#31yc" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32ct" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32ct')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32ct class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32ct" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31xt" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31xt" class="parent"><a name="31xt" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31xt" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31xt" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31xt" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/D_Alex/">D_Alex</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 09:36:36AM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31xt'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31xt')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31xt" class="" ><div class=