<p>-- The Poet Who Is Odd, <em><a href="http://www.asimovs.com/_issue_0401/knapsack.shtml" rel="nofollow">Knapsack Poems</a> by Elanor Arnason</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31x4"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31x4" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31x4')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31x4" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31x4')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31x4" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31x4?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31x4" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31x4')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31x4 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31x4" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31x4" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31x4" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_324m" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_324m" class="parent"><a name="324m" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_324m" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_324m" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_324m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Snowyowl/">Snowyowl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:00:28PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324m'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_324m')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_324m" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_324m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Snowyowl/">Snowyowl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:00:28PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_324m'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324m'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_324m')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_324m" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The mind boggles as to what he has actually done that is so strange on reflection.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Gentlemen, behold! I have made love to this machine! And now, upon retrospect, I ask why?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Dr. Weird, "Aqua Teen Hunger Force*</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_324m"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_324m" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324m')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_324m" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324m')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_324m" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/324m?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_324m" href="#31x4" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_324m" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_324m')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_324m class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_324m" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_324m" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_324m" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32cq" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32cq" class="parent"><a name="32cq" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32cq" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32cq" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32cq" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:01:02PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32cq'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32cq')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32cq" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32cq" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:01:02PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32cq'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32cq'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32cq')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32cq" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If you're curious, please read the story; it's short, and interesting! Actually, let me just spoil the premise now because I think it's neat and suspect other people will as well.</p>

<p><em>Knapsack Poems</em> is about an alien race called the goxhat, in which each "person" consists of around 10 individuals, of varying gender. There's no telepathy or anything cheap like that, it's just a cornerstone cultural meme for the goxhat.</p>

<p>So when The Poet Who Is Odd asks themself "Why did I do that?", it's <strong>not rhetorical</strong>. Arguing with oneself is not uncommon.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32cq"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32cq" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32cq')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32cq" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32cq')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32cq" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32cq?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32cq" href="#324m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32cq" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32cq')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32cq class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32cq" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32cq" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32cq" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_32d5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_32d5" class="parent"><a name="32d5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_32d5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_32d5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_32d5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/TheOtherDave/">TheOtherDave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:48:39PM</span><span class="votes " >7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32d5'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_32d5')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_32d5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_32d5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/TheOtherDave/">TheOtherDave</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 December 2010 08:48:39PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_32d5'>7 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_32d5'] = ['6 points', '7 points', '8 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_32d5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_32d5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's not necessarily rhetorical even for actual people in the real world. At least, I often find that when I ask myself questions and answer them out loud (or in writing), I get surprising answers. (Arguing with myself is not uncommon.)</p>

<p>Also, you might enjoy Vinge's <em>Fire Upon the Deep</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_32d5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_32d5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32d5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_32d5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_32d5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_32d5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/32d5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_32d5" href="#32cq" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_32d5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_32d5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_32d5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_32d5" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_32d5" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_32d5" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_34tb" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_34tb" class="parent"><a name="34tb" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_34tb" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_34tb" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_34tb" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 December 2010 03:22:41AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_34tb'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_34tb')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_34tb" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_34tb" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 December 2010 03:22:41AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_34tb'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_34tb'] = ['2 points', '3 poi