click="return hidecomment('t1_31w2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31w2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>The brighter you are, the more you have to learn.
-- Don Herold</p>

<p>I don't know the context of this, I came across it as a quote, but I can see two totally different interpretations, both true.</p>

<p>ADDED: Make that <em>five</em> interpretations.</p>

<p>The two I had in mind were:</p>

<p>Epistemic responsibility - you have an ethical obligation to learn because you can.</p>

<p>The more you <em>have to</em> learn - I don't know about you, but I am about as likely to stop learning as to stop breathing - I'm not likely to do either voluntarily.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_31w2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_31w2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31w2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_31w2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_31w2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_31w2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/31w2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_31w2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_31w2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_31w2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_31w2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_31w2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_31w2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_325f" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_325f" class="parent"><a name="325f" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_325f" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_325f" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_325f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 11:21:15PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_325f'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_325f')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_325f" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_325f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gjm/">gjm</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 11:21:15PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_325f'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_325f'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_325f')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_325f" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p><em>Three</em> interpretations.</p>

<ol>
<li>The brighter you are, the more there is for you to learn.</li>
<li>The brighter you are, the more there is that you need to learn.</li>
<li>The brighter you are, the more need there is for you to learn.</li>
</ol>

<p>(I hadn't noticed #3 until I read James Miller's comment.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_325f"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_325f" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_325f')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_325f" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_325f')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_325f" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/325f?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_325f" href="#31w2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_325f" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_325f')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_325f class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_325f" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_320f" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_320f" class="parent"><a name="320f" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_320f" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_320f" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_320f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_Miller/">James_Miller</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:26:31PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320f'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_320f')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_320f" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_320f" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/James_Miller/">James_Miller</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 04:26:31PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_320f'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_320f'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_320f')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_320f" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Why?  I can see why there is a greater marginal value to putting more time into learning if you are bright, but why is there a higher marginal value of learning more if you are bright especially if, like almost everything else, there is eventually diminishing marginal returns to learning and bright people know more than not bright people.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_320f"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_320f" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320f')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_320f" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_320f')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_320f" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/320f?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_320f" href="#31w2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_320f" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_320f')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_320f class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_320f" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_320f" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_320f" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_324u" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_324u" class="parent"><a name="324u" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_324u" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_324u" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_324u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Snowyowl/">Snowyowl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:06:21PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324u'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_324u')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_324u" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_324u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Snowyowl/">Snowyowl</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 10:06:21PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_324u'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_324u'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_324u')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_324u" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Bright people have more unanswered questions, maybe? You can't be pondering the Gibbs paradox without knowing much more about thermodynamics than I currently do.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_324u"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_324u" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324u')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_324u" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_324u')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_324u" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/37k/rationality_quotes_december_2010/324u?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_324u" href="#320f" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_324u" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_324u')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_324u class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_324u" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_31x6" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_31x6" class="parent"><a name="31x6" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_31x6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_31x6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_31x6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/anonym/">anonym</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 08:19:46AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31x6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_31x6')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_31x6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_31x6" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/anonym/">anonym</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 December 2010 08:19:46AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_31x6'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_31x6'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_31x6')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_31x6" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
